description.narrative: Emergency re-allocation of US$8.8 million from the over US$85 million Health System Strengthening (HSS-2) Gavi-funded programme was crucial to Myanmar's effective response to COVID-19 and the quick resumption of life-saving services by the Ministry of Health and Sports. While preventing COVID-19 transmission and ensuring continuity of services, focus has been given to improve quality of care delivered to sick children in UNICEF's supported district hospitals across prioritized states/regions. Case management and infection prevention and controls in these hospitals were also supported to ensure continuity of routine services, quality of newborn and paediatric care provided through these hospitals. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/07/2020
